277
00:12:26,788 --> 00:12:29,374
Now eat up
before it gets cold.

278
00:12:29,374 --> 00:12:32,210
Hargh, easy, Mom.

279
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,128
Arrgh!

280
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:46,224
♪

281
00:12:46,224 --> 00:12:47,016
I don't get how being

282
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:48,601
flipped on my butt
for three hours

283
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,520
counts as extra training.

284
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:54,399
Ugh, all 'cause I helped
out that little kid.

285
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:56,025
Good morning, Gao.

286
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:57,235
Huh?

287
00:12:57,235 --> 00:12:59,654
Kuguro and Baku.

288
00:12:59,654 --> 00:13:01,239
Hey, what's up?

289
00:13:01,239 --> 00:13:03,741
Not much, I was
just asking Baku here

290
00:13:03,741 --> 00:13:05,868
that if he could
chose buddy at all,

291
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:07,578
which world would
he chose from?

292
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:09,080
That's a good question.

293
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:11,457
Baku said he's never even
thought about it before

294
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:14,085
since, you know, he's
a deck builder and all.

295
00:13:14,085 --> 00:13:16,254
Yeah, well, I'm sure
there's a lot of things

296
00:13:16,254 --> 00:13:17,422
he hasn't thought about.

297
00:13:17,422 --> 00:13:20,675
Yeah, right, look who's
talking, Mr. Sun Fighter.

298
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:22,552
(growling)

299
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:25,638
So, what about you, Gao?

300
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:27,098
The Dragon World?

301
00:13:27,098 --> 00:13:29,225
The Magic Worlds?

302
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:32,145
Or the Danger Worlds?

303
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:34,355
Not an easy choice, huh?

304
00:13:34,355 --> 00:13:36,941
Hmm, let me think.

305
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:39,610
My monster'd have
to have a big weapon.

306
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:41,612
Something he'd use
to crush anything

307
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:43,156
standing in our way.

308
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:46,325
So the world I'd pick for
such a choice monster is,

309
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:49,370
well, I don't know,
that's a tough one.

310
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:51,289
But as long as
he's mega strong,

311
00:13:51,289 --> 00:13:53,291
it doesn't really matter.

312
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:55,209
How about a dragon knight?

313
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:58,254
Hmm, was that
a dragon knight?

314
00:13:58,254 --> 00:13:59,422
Not sure about that,

315
00:13:59,422 --> 00:14:01,340
but the dragon
Jackknife's pretty cool.

316
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:03,718
I never pegged you
for a dragon.

317
00:14:03,718 --> 00:14:05,178
(snickering)

318
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:07,638
Ah, no way,
no way, no way!

319
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,307
I can't become
buddies with a guy

320
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:11,726
who runs away
from his fights.

321
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:14,353
Oh, yeah, dragons
are the only way to go,

322
00:14:14,353 --> 00:14:16,064
trust me.

323
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:17,565
You like dragons, huh?

324
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:19,358
Huh, Noboru?

325
00:14:19,358 --> 00:14:22,111
They're okay, but dragon knights
are way cooler.

326
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:24,781
Dragons are nothing
without their masters.

327
00:14:24,781 --> 00:14:27,950
What is a dragon knight?

328
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,118
Take a look.

329
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:30,995
They're humans
that ride on dragons

330
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:33,247
and bravely fight
along side them.

331
00:14:33,247 --> 00:14:34,999
Dragons are just
dim‐witted monsters

332
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:36,667
that couldn't even
find their own tails

333
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:39,670
without being ordered
to by a dragon knight.

334
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:40,880
Kind of lame, really.

335
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,758
Aaah, dragons
are dim‐witted?

336
00:14:43,758 --> 00:14:45,510
Can't find
their own tails?

337
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:47,011
dragon knights
are weaklings!

338
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:48,221
All they do is
bark out orders

339
00:14:48,221 --> 00:14:50,431
as if we don't
know what to do!

340
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:51,641
Listen up, kid.

341
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:53,059
Why don't you tell
your drooly friend there

342
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:56,354
why dragons are far
superior to dragon knights?

343
00:14:56,354 --> 00:14:59,440
Yeah, maybe Noboru's right.

344
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,526
What is wrong with you?

345
00:15:01,526 --> 00:15:02,401
Aaagh!

346
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,362
(splashing)

347
00:15:04,362 --> 00:15:07,865
Dragons are the most
extraordinary creatures ever.

348
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:10,034
I'll have to show them.

349
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:12,703
Hurry, or we'll be late.

350
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:14,539
Leave him behind.

351
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,999
Come on, just hang on
a sec, would you, guys?

352
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,292
Gah!

353
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,211
Morning, class.

354
00:15:20,211 --> 00:15:22,547
Today I have something
very exciting planned.

355
00:15:22,547 --> 00:15:23,798
We're going to write essays

356
00:15:23,798 --> 00:15:26,342
using a buddyfight
card pack.

357
00:15:26,342 --> 00:15:28,219
I'd like you to
create short stories

358
00:15:28,219 --> 00:15:29,887
using the monsters
you find inside

359
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:32,890
and make one of them
your main character.

360
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:35,560
Yeah, I got a
double rare card!

361
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:37,186
Ha, I can't believe it!

362
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:42,024
Check it out, a
Dragon Knight Maximillian.

363
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:44,735
Uh, maybe I've got one too.

364
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:47,238
A Systemic Dagger Dragon.

365
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:49,532
Okay.

366
00:15:49,532 --> 00:15:51,075
Next one is...

367
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:55,538
ah, a Lotale
Shield Dragon!

368
00:15:55,538 --> 00:15:57,790
(chewing)

369
00:15:57,790 --> 00:16:00,251
And a Thousand
Rapier Dragon!

370
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:02,003
Man, all of
these monster cards

371
00:16:02,003 --> 00:16:03,337
are so totally cool!

372
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:06,382
Ha, none of them are rare
though, are they, pal?

373
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:07,633
It doesn't matter.

374
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:10,553
Picking a double rare card
is beyond you anyways.

375
00:16:10,553 --> 00:16:13,264
I mean, it takes
a lot of skill.

376
00:16:13,264 --> 00:16:15,474
And now for the last card.

377
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:19,228
♪

378
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:20,771
‐Ah!
‐Oh!

379
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:22,815
What's happening?

380
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:25,902
Hey, wait,
that's my card!

381
00:16:25,902 --> 00:16:28,613
Buddy monster reaction
is confirmed, sir.

382
00:16:28,613 --> 00:16:31,324
In the 700 block of
West Tokyo district,

383
00:16:31,324 --> 00:16:33,451
on the grounds of
Aibo School Academy.

384
00:16:33,451 --> 00:16:34,452
It looks like
the monster is

385
00:16:34,452 --> 00:16:37,163
Armor Dragon,
Drum Bunker Dragon.

386
00:16:37,163 --> 00:16:37,830
Huh?

387
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:39,582
Are you quite
sure about that?

388
00:16:39,582 --> 00:16:40,082
Yes.

389
00:16:40,082 --> 00:16:41,792
‐(beeping)
‐Huh?

390
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:49,133
♪

391
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:49,967
Come back!

392
00:16:49,967 --> 00:17:06,984
♪

393
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:09,528
(oohing and aahing)

394
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:13,449
♪

395
00:17:13,449 --> 00:17:15,493
All of a sudden now
you have nothing to say?

396
00:17:15,493 --> 00:17:16,535
Ah?

397
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:32,009
♪

398
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:36,097
Yes, it's a dragon!

399
00:17:36,097 --> 00:17:38,140
You've got to be joking.

400
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:40,893
♪

401
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:42,436
What are you
trying to pull, kid?

402
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:43,437
Just a handshake.

403
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:46,524
You are gonna be
my buddy, aren't you?

404
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:48,109
Hah, not if
I can help it.

405
00:17:48,109 --> 00:17:49,110
Huh?

406
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,528
But you came
out of my card.

407
00:17:50,528 --> 00:17:54,365
Doesn't that mean you
have to be my buddy?

408
00:17:54,365 --> 00:17:55,366
You think dragon knights

409
00:17:55,366 --> 00:17:58,244
are better than
dragons, do ya?

410
00:17:58,244 --> 00:18:00,162
Or maybe I misheard you.

411
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:01,956
Well, I, uh, you know.

412
00:18:01,956 --> 00:18:03,291
I'm waiting.

413
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:05,710
♪

414
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:07,086
Why do you listen
to that insolent

415
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:08,254
little friend of yours?

416
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:11,257
How dare he call me
a dim‐witted monster?

417
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:13,050
‐Well, Noboro?
‐You lucked out.

418
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:16,345
How does a guy like you
draw a buddy rare monster?

419
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:17,388
I just can't believe it.

420
00:18:17,388 --> 00:18:19,557
It's so unfair.

421
00:18:19,557 --> 00:18:21,225
Come on, don't be that way.

422
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:22,643
Huh?

423
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:23,978
I may not be the smartest,

424
00:18:23,978 --> 00:18:25,521
or know everything
that you do,

425
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:26,647
but luck or no luck,

426
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:28,232
the trick
is to keep trying

427
00:18:28,232 --> 00:18:31,611
and go after what
you really want.

428
00:18:31,611 --> 00:18:34,071
Hmm.

429
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:35,990
Right?

430
00:18:35,990 --> 00:18:37,533
Hey, don't you look at me.

431
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:38,784
I'm still ticked
'cause you believed

432
00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:40,911
that whining
sore loser over there.

433
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,038
You want to buddy with me?

434
00:18:42,038 --> 00:18:43,581
You better
show some respect.

435
00:18:43,581 --> 00:18:44,332
Huh?

436
00:18:44,332 --> 00:18:47,585
(loud flapping)

437
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,757
It's Jackknife Dragon.

438
00:18:52,757 --> 00:18:54,842
‐Ha!
‐Whoa!

439
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,427
Sorry to just
drop in on you.

440
00:18:56,427 --> 00:18:57,428
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

441
00:18:57,428 --> 00:19:00,931
♪

442
00:19:00,931 --> 00:19:03,934
But actually, I'm here
on official business.

443
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:05,686
Do you know
who I am?

444
00:19:05,686 --> 00:19:08,272
Tasuku Ryuenji!

445
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:11,317
(excited murmuring)

446
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:18,324
Tasuku and Jack from
the Buddy Police are here!

447
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:20,743
Look, there's Jack!

448
00:19:20,743 --> 00:19:23,287
Well, I guess in the future
I should have you come

449
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:24,580
in mini form, huh?

450
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:28,000
You're right,
but I'd refuse.

451
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,961
Tasuku Ryuenji, the boy
wonder from the Buddy Police!

452
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:32,838
Why's he here
at our school?

453
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:34,256
Listen in and find out!

454
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:36,342
You're live with
school reporter extraordinaire,

455
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:38,594
Paruko Nanana, and her
faithful buddy sidekick

456
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:42,348
the one and only Hero World
Martian UFO, Takosuke!

457
00:19:42,348 --> 00:19:44,558
Come on out, Takosuke!

458
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:46,102
♪

459
00:19:46,102 --> 00:19:48,062
Tako‐chuuu!

460
00:19:48,062 --> 00:19:49,313
Let's go!

461
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:51,482
♪

462
00:19:51,482 --> 00:19:54,819
You're on active duty
or just come to see me?

463
00:19:54,819 --> 00:19:56,570
To be honest, I came
here to deliver this

464
00:19:56,570 --> 00:19:59,657
Core Deck Case to Gao.

465
00:19:59,657 --> 00:20:02,284
Here, this
belongs to you now.

466
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:04,745
It can be transformed
into a core gadget,

467
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:07,748
which will allow you
to illuminize your deck.

468
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:10,042
Go on, take it.

469
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,752
Illuminize?

470
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:14,046
Any human who becomes
buddies with a monster

471
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:17,133
is given a Core Deck Case
from the buddy card office.

472
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:20,261
Didn't you know that?

473
00:20:20,261 --> 00:20:22,930
And yes, of course,
I have one too.

474
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:26,434
♪

475
00:20:26,434 --> 00:20:27,977
Gee, thanks.

476
00:20:27,977 --> 00:20:31,188
♪

477
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:33,649
This also makes you
an official buddyfighter.

478
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:34,859
Huh?

479
00:20:34,859 --> 00:20:37,111
You're now able to go out
and buddyfight with monsters

480
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:40,030
at any time and any place
that you want.

481
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:42,783
Buddyfight with monsters?

482
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:43,826
Well, bye.

483
00:20:43,826 --> 00:20:47,455
No, hang on,
where are you going?

484
00:20:47,455 --> 00:20:49,415
What if I challenged
you to a fight

485
00:20:49,415 --> 00:20:50,583
to help train me?

486
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:52,710
♪

487
00:20:52,710 --> 00:20:55,296
Sorry, did I hear
you correctly?

488
00:20:55,296 --> 00:20:57,047
You'd like to
buddyfight challenge me

489
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:59,216
and Jack from
the Buddy Police?

490
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:03,262
Yeah, well, you know,
if you're up for it?

491
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:04,972
(murmuring)

492
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:06,265
What a total dweeb.

493
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,517
It's too soon to be
challenging Master Tasuku

494
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:11,562
of the Buddy Police,
don't you think?

495
00:21:11,562 --> 00:21:14,231
It's a no‐brainer that you
will be completely destroyed!

496
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:16,650
Use your head, kid,
it's common sense, right?

497
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,694
Forgive me if I don't
listen to common sense

498
00:21:18,694 --> 00:21:21,489
coming from a girl
in a UFO.

499
00:21:21,489 --> 00:21:23,407
Common sense?

500
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:29,205
It should be someone
who's unconventional.

501
00:21:29,205 --> 00:21:30,247
Hmm.

502
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:35,795
But it's Jackknife Dragon.

503
00:21:35,795 --> 00:21:37,505
Uh, whatever.

504
00:21:37,505 --> 00:21:39,590
I have to try.

505
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:42,760
I must know my potential.

506
00:21:45,346 --> 00:21:48,599
Hey you, little human?

507
00:21:48,599 --> 00:21:50,893
From this moment on,

508
00:21:50,893 --> 00:21:53,479
you and I will be buddies.

509
00:21:53,479 --> 00:21:55,856
Did you say buddies?

510
00:21:55,856 --> 00:21:57,191
Yes!

511
00:21:57,191 --> 00:21:58,275
I am none other
than the son

512
00:21:58,275 --> 00:22:00,528
of the honorable
Drum Bunker Dragon,

513
00:22:00,528 --> 00:22:02,988
Fang Slade Terrestrial,
the Thirteenth.

514
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,407
How about I just
call you Drum?

515
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:07,326
Yeah, well
how about you don't!

516
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:09,912
Heh, whatevs,
I'm the leader.

517
00:22:09,912 --> 00:22:13,999
The name's Gao,
Gao Mikado.

518
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:25,719
♪

519
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:27,137
You can still take
back your challenge

520
00:22:27,137 --> 00:22:28,973
if you want to.

521
00:22:28,973 --> 00:22:31,267
I don't want
to take it back.

522
00:22:31,267 --> 00:22:34,353
I don't know why, but
I know I have to do this.

523
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:38,148
♪

524
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:40,818
That's why I'd
like to challenge you

525
00:22:40,818 --> 00:22:44,154
to a buddyfight
right here and now.

526
00:22:44,154 --> 00:22:48,742
♪

527
00:22:49,702 --> 00:22:51,829
Hello there,
I'm Paruko Nanana,

528
00:22:51,829 --> 00:22:54,331
your guide to the
buddyfight world.

529
00:22:54,331 --> 00:22:55,749
Every episode
will introduce you

530
00:22:55,749 --> 00:22:57,710
to some buddyfight
fun facts

531
00:22:57,710 --> 00:22:58,836
and some super
cool techniques

532
00:22:58,836 --> 00:23:00,170
that you can use at home.

533
00:23:00,170 --> 00:23:03,007
Today we focused on
our own world, Earth.

534
00:23:03,007 --> 00:23:05,426
As you saw, Gao's
buddy card got connected

535
00:23:05,426 --> 00:23:07,386
to the Dragon World
and he met Drum.

536
00:23:07,386 --> 00:23:09,138
That's 'cause buddy
cards are like portals

537
00:23:09,138 --> 00:23:10,556
for monsters
from other worlds

538
00:23:10,556 --> 00:23:11,974
to come hang out on Earth.

539
00:23:11,974 --> 00:23:14,685
It's totally epic,
don't you think?

540
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:15,644
What do you think, guys,

541
00:23:15,644 --> 00:23:19,690
can you open
a buddy rare card?

542
00:23:19,690 --> 00:24:47,569
♪

